description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;Chapelwood Primary Care Centre, Rogerstone, Newport, South Wales&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a well established, friendly and forward thinking training Practice who are committed to high quality care and the continued development of our Practice workforce. We are seeking to recruit an experienced and highly motivated Practice Nurse with a Diploma in Minor Illness to work as part of our very experienced and supportive healthcare team. Good communication skills and a flexible approach is vital. .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Required duties include health promotion, Asthma, COPD, Spirometry, Cytology, family planning, menopause management, wound care, leg ulcer management, removal of sutures, ear irrigation, competent in ECG and Doppler procedures and routine vaccinations. A diploma in Minor Illness is preferable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12,530 Patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modern purpose built premises&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Easy access, the practice is situated just off junctions 28 and 27 on the M4&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7 Partners, 5 Nurses (including Minor Illness and Nurse led Chronic Disease Clinics), 2 HCA and excellent Administration Team&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Training Practice - 2 GP Registrars&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful applicants will be expected to work autonomously with support from the Senior Practice Nurse and GP Partners, and participate in an annual individual performance review. This includes taking responsibility for maintaining a record of own personal and continuing professional development plan for revalidation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Current NMC registration will be required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An enhanced disclosure barring service check will be undertaken by the practice which will meet the cost of the check.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Informal enquiries to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;David Harris, Practice Manager/ Diane George, Senior Practice Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Rogerstone Practice, Chapelwood Primary Care Centre, Rogerstone, Newport NP10 9DU&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 01633 890800&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: david.harris4@wales.nhs.uk/ diane.george2@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
